---
/**
 * §3 — One Connected Business System.
 * Carries the wider capability explanation that is deliberately kept OUT of
 * the hero (Gate 1 §6). This is where breadth is allowed to appear — and it
 * appears connected, not as a list.
 */

const DOMAINS = [
  { k: 'Market & opportunity', d: 'Where demand actually exists, and whether the gap is structural or cosmetic.' },
  { k: 'Business model & go-to-market', d: 'Who pays, why they join, what sequence makes the launch survivable.' },
  { k: 'Operations & process', d: 'Ownership, handoffs, exceptions, capacity — and the work that should stop existing.' },
  { k: 'Customer experience & support', d: 'Contact drivers as evidence. Why customers had to ask at all.' },
  { k: 'Conversion & journey UI/UX', d: 'Information timing, trust, decision clarity — judged commercially, not visually.' },
  { k: 'Product & feature strategy', d: 'What earns a build. What earns a sentence instead.' },
  { k: 'Growth & funnel economics', d: 'Offer, margin, order quality, and whether acquisition is even the constraint.' },
  { k: 'Cross-functional execution', d: 'Briefs, sequencing, QA, and the measurement defined before launch.' },
  { k: 'AI-aware decisions', d: 'When to automate, when to build, and when the disciplined answer is neither.' },
];
---

<section class="section zone-stone bsys" id="system" aria-labelledby="bsys-h">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">The connecting principle</span>
      <h2 id="bsys-h" class="sec-head__q">Customers experience one business — not separate departments.</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Marketing may attract the customer, the website may shape the decision, operations may
        fulfil the promise, support may explain what was unclear, and product may receive the
        feature request. I connect these signals before deciding where the problem actually belongs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <blockquote class="bsys__stmt">
      <p class="statement">I do not optimize the symptom. I trace the system that keeps producing it.</p>
    </blockquote>

    <div class="bsys__grid">
      {DOMAINS.map((d) => (
        <div class="bsys__cell">
          <h3 class="bsys__k">{d.k}</h3>
          <p class="bsys__d">{d.d}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="bsys__rule">
      These are not nine services. They are nine places one system can lose value — which is
      why the diagnosis has to start before the solution.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .bsys__stmt {
    margin: 0 0 var(--s7);
    padding: var(--s5) 0 var(--s5) var(--s5);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--teal-deep);
    max-width: 40ch;
  }
  .bsys__stmt .statement { color: var(--stone-ink); }

  .bsys__grid {
    display: grid; gap: 0;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-stone);
    border-left: 1px solid var(--hairline-stone);
  }
  .bsys__cell {
    padding: var(--s5);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--hairline-stone);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-stone);
  }
  .bsys__k { font-size: var(--fs-h4); margin-bottom: var(--s2); }
  .bsys__d { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--stone-muted); }
  .bsys__rule {
    margin-top: var(--s6); max-width: var(--measure);
    font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--stone-muted);
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .bsys__grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .bsys__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
